    Error translating content. Please try again later.
    WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter was a class in Spring Security that has been deprecated since Spring Security 5.7 and completely removed in version 6.0. It was used for configuring web security, but the recommended modern approach is to use a component-based configuration with a SecurityFilterChain bean instead.
     
    What it was
    • WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter was the base class for creating Spring Security configurations.
    • Developers would extend this class and override methods like configure(HttpSecurity) to define rules for different parts of their application.
    • The goal was to customize authentication, authorization, and other security settings for different URL patterns. 
    Why it was deprecated
    • Inflexibility:
      The adapter-based approach was less flexible and could be difficult to use in complex scenarios. 
    • Component-based approach:
      The Spring team moved to a more component-based configuration with SecurityFilterChain beans, which is more modern, flexible, and easier to manage. 
    • Conflict:
      Using the new component-based approach and the old adapter approach in the same project is not allowed and will cause errors. 
    • WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter is deprecated since Spring Security ...
      Jun 14, 2022 0 deprecated the WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter and moved to a component-based configuration. The problem is that you ca...
      GitHub
    What to do now
    • Migrate:
      If you are using an older version of Spring Security or Spring Boot, you will need to migrate your configuration to the new component-based approach. 
    • Use SecurityFilterChain:
      The new way to configure security is by defining a SecurityFilterChain bean, which is a more declarative and flexible approach. 
    • Consult resources:
      For guidance on migration, you can find many articles and videos that explain how to transition from WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter to the new style of configuration.

      What is the use of a WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter?
      Creates an instance which allows specifying if the default configuration should be enabled. Disabling the default configuration should be considered more advanced usage as it requires more understanding of how the framework is implemented.
